    "Writing that enzymes are 'used up' or 'alive' — catalysts are not used up (heat can denature them, which is different).",
    "Listing the gall bladder, liver or pancreas as part of the alimentary canal — they are accessory organs; food never passes through them.",
    "Saying bile 'digests' or 'breaks down' fat — bile emulsifies fat (physical), it is lipase that chemically digests it.",
